M|Exam|tx|See `examples/sample.md` for full roadmap examples.
M|Exam|Mini|
M|Exam|tx|```markdown
M|Exam|Now|Guided onboarding (activation +20%)
M|Exam|nx|Enterprise SSO (deal velocity)
M|Exam|Late|Mobile workflows (DAU lift)
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Pitf|**Sy|** Roadmap lists features ("Dark mode," "SSO," "Advanced filters") w/ no context
M|Pitf|**Co|** No st clarity, stakeholders don't understand "why"
M|Pitf|fix|** Frame epics as hypotheses w/ sc metrics (not just feature names)
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** Execs dictate roadmap, no data-driven prioritization
M|Pitf|**Co|** bd wrong things, ignore cs problems
M|Pitf|fix|** Use prioritization framework (RICE, ICE) to transparently score epics
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** Roadmap treated as contract, no flexibility to adjust
M|Pitf|**Co|** Can't pivot when you learn new information
M|Pitf|fix|** Communicate roadmap as "st plan, subject to change based on learning"
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** Sequence epics w/o checking tc dependencies
M|Pitf|**Co|** Q2 epic blk bc Q1 dependency didn't finish
M|Pitf|fix|** Map dependencies explicitly in Phase 4, validate w/ engineering
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** PM creates roadmap alone, presents finished plan
M|Pitf|**Co|** No buy-in, stakeholders feel excluded
M|Pitf|fix|** Gather inputs (Phase 1) from all stakeholders, present draft (Phase 5) for feedback
M|Pitf|tx|---
